messageBody:
I see now that my last post referred to a file uploaded to the Shavian
website rather than Read_Alphabet which I assumed it to be to at first
glance. I converted the file to "Jerome" and did not realize that it
was a Shavian file. Presumably, most of you did not receive it. I
don't have a Shavian font on this computer, but my suspicion is that the
mistakes I detected also exist in the Shavian version as I don't believe
they involved any of the letters in the two alphabets that are different
from each other.

Nevertheless, I believe the point of my post was valid: we all should
guard against TO affecting our QS writing.

Paige

P.S. for those of you old enough to remember the early Saturday Night
Live shows, I feel like Emily Litella -- "Never mind."
